## 1. `TenantOnboardingService::complete()` method

**File:** `/Users/arthur/Devel/WorkSpaceAI/framework/multi_tenant_saas/src/Services/TenantOnboardingService.php`

- **Method signature:** line **230** вҖ” `public function complete(string $token): Tenant`
- **Session load & validation:** lines 232-245 (loads session from Cache, rejects if null/already-completed/missing-steps)
- **Data extraction:** lines 247-253 (pulls STEP_BASIC_INFO, STEP_DOMAIN, STEP_PLAN; resolves plan and trial flag)
- **DB transaction block:** lines **255-272** вҖ” creates Tenant, default roles (admin/user), admin User, TenantUser join, provisions TenantSetting, optionally starts trial via `TrialService::startTrial()`
- **Post-transaction:** lines 274-286 вҖ” marks Cache session completed, sets `current_step = STEP_COMPLETE` and `tenant_id`, forgets email index, dispatches `TenantCreated` event, returns `$tenant`
- **Key design note:** `complete()` does **not** write `onboarding_step` or `onboarding_completed` on the Tenant model. The `createTenant()` helper (line 292-315) sets status, slug, plan, etc. but omits those two columns. They remain at their DB defaults (`0` / `false`).

